reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great design with metal drawer slides
reviews.reviewText: Very happy with this purchase. I'm using it in my craft room. I originally bought two large plastic containers with drawers but didn't like the look of it. Returned them and found this. Very sturdy and looks so much better. It did take a long time to put together. But it was easy. It's all labeled and has clear instructions. It's made with metal drawers slides which makes it way sturdier than others.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars B sure you have time before starting this project
reviews.reviewText: I gave this product 4 stars bc of minor imperfections (misalignments) drawer didn’t line up and had to use a mallet foot correction so the drawer base could slide into the slot.Next, I read all the blah about it taking 3 hours to assemble. I’m a carpenter by trade and very handy but that doesn’t matter it takes one person at least 2.5hrs to assemble. On a positive note, the piece is very sturdy, very sleek design nice curvature and crisp edges and seems like it’s built to last a while and for the price I give it b 4.5/5. Started project at 15:40 finished 18:49.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars only if patient, room to work, and time
reviews.reviewText: This is a lovely and sturdy piece, it was delivered early and right before a snow storm, so I had a day off work to just focus on it. It took me about four hours to complete on my own with a tv going. If you go slow and lay out all the pieces it will help, IF YOU ARE NOT ABLE TO GET THE SCREWS flushed with the drawer railing/sliders then keep trying or remove the screw. On a few of my rails, they only have two screws instead of three because I could not get it flushed and that teeny tiny issue would keep the wheels from rolling and the drawers not being able to open so you have to very forcibly remove the drawers and keep trying. Once I figured it out and removed the screw(s) the drawers glide effortlessly. Very solid piece and looks pricey but it was some work.
